A Hidden Infrastructure
Beneath every ecosystem on Earth is an underground circulatory system: complex, dense networks of underground fungi that move massive amounts of carbon and nutrients, regulating the climate and feeding plants above ground. But what is the global scale of all this hidden infrastructure, and how is it distributed? Until recently, no one really knew.
