jun 11, 2026
A new interactive map, created by SPUN, along with new research published in Science, provides the first real estimate of the enormity and distribution of Earth’s arbuscular mycorrhizal fungal networks. The research was produced by an international team led by SPUN researcher Justin Stewart and Corentin Bisot of the AMOLF Physics Institute. The data, available for downloading, can help scientists and decision-makers begin to determine which of these vital fungal systems are thriving, which may need help, and which clearly need more sampling.
It also offers compelling surprises.
